[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_qmfwa")
reagent_id = "H2S"
title = "Hydrogen Sulfide"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]H₂S[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]34 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]Gas[/cell]
[cell]Color:[/cell][cell]Colorless[/cell]
[cell]Smell:[/cell][cell]Strong smell of rotten eggs[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reactions[/b]
H₂ + S → H₂S  
H₂ + SO₂ → H₂S + H₂O
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Toxic gas.
• Flammable and can burn in oxygen.
• Slightly acidic when dissolved in water.
[b]Where hydrogen sulfide is found[/b]
• In volcanic gases and hot springs.
• Produced by decomposition of organic matter.
• Found in some natural gas and petroleum deposits.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Used in chemical laboratories.
• Important in the production of sulfur and sulfur compounds.
[b]Safety[/b]
Very toxic and dangerous in high concentrations.
Can affect the nervous system and breathing."
